      <div class="about-section-content">
            <p>At present Folly Farm is open. We think holidays are important and the chance to get away from the noise and clutter of everyday life is fundamentally healthy. 
            The space and natural surroundings here will feel refreshing and at present we won't take that away. We are taking the advice of medical professionals, the government and governing bodies seriously and alongside this believe we have a duty of care to our campers, our local community and our team.</p>

<p>While the risk of Covid-19 continues if you are planning  on camping please consider the following;</p>

<p>Call or email us if you have any symptoms or feel you need to cancel your stay due to Covid-19, we are ready to move your holiday to another date or issue a credit voucher that will be valid for 18 months. Our normal terms and conditions will apply for refunds. If there are any restrictions placed on travel or gatherings of people then we will review and let you know.</p>

<p>If you believe that you are vulnerable, or have regular close contact with anyone who is please consider carefully if this is the time for you to come on holiday.</p>

<p>You cannot self-isolate at Folly Farm for the safety of other campers, our team and our community.</p>

<p>Use common sense hygiene practice while here. Wash your hands and bin your tissues. Remember that the facilities are communal and help reduce the risk for our other campers and team. If you are in a caravan or motor home, please use your own facilities as much as possible. We will, as always, keep the facilities clean and use disinfectant.</p>

<p>If you develop symptoms while on the site, please refrain from using the facilities. Please pack up and call the office to notify that you are leaving the site.</p>
